# ft_irc

An Internet Relay Chat (IRC) server implementation following RFC 2812 specifications.

## Usage
```bash
make
./ircserv <port> <password>
```

## Features
- TCP/IP socket programming
- Non-blocking I/O with poll()
- Client authentication
- Channel operations
- Private messaging
- User modes
- Channel modes
- Operator privileges
- Nickname management
- Command parsing

## Supported Commands
- `/join`: Join channels
- `/part`: Leave channels
- `/quit`: Disconnect
- `/nick`: Change nickname
- `/privmsg`: Send messages
- `/notice`: Send notices
- `/kick`: Remove users
- `/invite`: Invite users
- `/topic`: Manage channel topics
- `/mode`: Set modes
- `/who`: Query user info
- `/whois`: Detailed user info

## Technical Details
- C++ implementation
- RFC 2812 compliant
- Socket programming
- Multiple client handling
- Buffer management
- Error handling
- Memory management

## Project Structure
```
ft_irc/
├── Bot/
├── includes/
├── server/
│   └── irc.hpp
└── Makefile
```

## Testing
- Compatible with standard IRC clients
- Tested with:
  - irssi
  - WeeChat
  - NetCat

## Error Handling
- Socket errors
- Client disconnection
- Invalid commands
- Permission checks
- Buffer overflow protection
